28/02/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia was formally admitted to the Central European Free Trade Agreement (CEFTA) on Monday (27 February), becoming the organisation's fourth member after Bulgaria, Croatia and Romania.
Economy Minister Fatmir Besimi said the move represents a step forward in the EU accession process.
The document awaits ratification by the Macedonian Parliament.
In other news, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski was scheduled to wrap up a two-day visit to Bucharest on Tuesday.
Romanian counterpart Traian Basescu reiterated his country's support for Macedonia's EU and NATO accession bids and its readiness to provide assistance in meeting EU membership criteria.
(Nine o'clock - 28/02/06;
Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 27/02/06)
